author: Unknown
content_text:
Closure Notice â€“ Operations Update
To our valued community,
It is with much regret that the Linear Operations Team now write to advise you to leave the project. Many of us have worked alongside you for nearly five years, and we share in the disappointment this brings. While this outcome was not what anyone hoped for, we remain committed to supporting all users during this transition, within the boundaries of the instructions provided by the projectâ€™s owners and investors.
Below youâ€™ll find the essential details to help you safely exit your positions, along with the key dates to be aware of. If you need assistance, support remains available until the closure dateâ€”primarily via our Telegram group, and secondarily on Discord.
Exit Your Positions
We strongly recommend that all users exit their positions as soon as possible. Liquidity will become increasingly limited over time. Additionally, once Binance completes the delisting of the LINA token, market access may be further reduced.
Shutdown Timeline
Final Closure: Weds, 2 April 2025 at 12:00 PM UTC
At this time, the Linear suite of dApps will go offline, except for a Burn and Unstake Portal, which will remain available to:
- Unstake tokens from staking and exit
- Burn LUSD, if necessary, to clear debt and enable unstaking
Immediate Actions to Take
Locked Staking Rewards
All remaining locked and vesting rewards (originally scheduled to vest over the next 12 months) have been moved to your staked balance. These can now be unstaked and withdrawn, subject to your debt position.
Builder
Repay any outstanding Builder debt and unstake any collateral (LINA or other tokens).
Synthetic Exchange
Remaining liquid assets should be converted to LUSD via the Synthetic Exchange, and then sold on PancakeSwap. Terminal prices for all liquid assets have already been applied. Only conversions into LUSD are now supported.
Bridge
The ETH/BSC and BSC/ETH bridges for LINA and LUSD will close permanently at shutdown. No cross-chain transfers will be possible after this point.
Liquidator
The Liquidator has already been switched off
Marketplace
The Marketplace has already been closed. No active listings remain, aside from those previously managed by the team.
PerpDEX
The PerpDEX will be shut down at the closure time. All users must exit positions and withdraw funds well in advance to avoid potential loss.
Community Channels
Telegram and Discord will remain open until the shutdown date, after which the chat functionality will be disabled.
Thank you for being part of the Linear Finance journey. We are here to support you during this final phase. Please remain respectful to all team members throughout this process.
Sincerely,
The Linear Operations Team

content_text:
Why Was Todayâ€™s $CAKE Burn So Bigâ“

Every Monday, PancakeSwap conducts its routine CAKE burn, removing a portion of the total supply to help maintain tokenomics and sustainability. However, todayâ€™s burn was significantly larger than usual. Hereâ€™s why.

Understanding the CAKE Minting and Burning Process

CAKE tokens are minted and temporarily held in the MasterChef V2 (MCV2) contract. This contract distributes CAKE as farm rewards when users harvest their yields. Typically, when someone claims their rewards, the system also triggers the burncake() function, which removes some of the supply.

New CAKE is only minted if MCV2 doesnâ€™t have enough tokens to distribute. Since MCV2 is often running low, calling burncake() normally leads to the minting of millions of CAKE, with a portion allocated for burning.

What Happened Today?

During todayâ€™s burncake() call, MCV2 already had approximately 3 million CAKE available.

Key Differences in Today's Burn:
- No new CAKE was minted.
- The entire 3 million CAKE in MCV2 was sent to Burn Safe for burning.

Why Was There So Much CAKE in MCV2?

The most likely explanation is the Ecosystem Fund. These funds were minted earlier but were accumulating in MCV2 since there was no immediate need to use them. Because MCV2 had enough CAKE available for distribution, these tokens remained untouched until today's scheduled burn.

Final Thoughts

Today's burn was an unusual but positive event for CAKEâ€™s supply dynamics. Instead of minting and burning new tokens, previously minted CAKE was directly removed from circulation. This means fewer new tokens were introduced into the system, potentially reducing inflationary pressure.

With PancakeSwap's commitment to efficient tokenomics, such events reinforce the platformâ€™s long-term sustainability. Stay tuned for more updates on CAKE burns and supply changes!

$CAKE PancakeSwap MEV Guard: Secure and Smart Swap Experience!!

PancakeSwap has introduced an important update to its MEV Guard feature, enhancing protection against MEV (Miner Extractable Value) attacks on the BNB Chain. With this update, support has been expanded to include Binance Wallet, Trust Wallet, OKX Wallet, and Rabby Wallet, making it even easier to trade safely.

What is MEV Guard?

MEV attacks occur when bots manipulate transactions, often leading to worse prices and failed swaps. PancakeSwap MEV Guard prevents frontrunning and sandwich attacks, ensuring a fair trading experience for all users.

Key Features

- Protection against MEV attacks for safer swaps
- Fast and reliable RPC for smooth transactions
- Free and easy setup with one-click activation
- Expanded wallet support, including Binance Wallet, Trust Wallet, OKX Wallet, MetaMask, and Rabby Wallet

How to Enable MEV Guard

Binance Wallet and Trust Wallet (Automatic Activation)
1. Connect your Binance Wallet or Trust Wallet to PancakeSwap.
2. Check for the "MEV Protected" label on the swap page.

MetaMask and OKX Wallet (One-Click Setup)
1. Visit the PancakeSwap MEV Guard page.
2. Connect your wallet.
3. Click "Enable MEV Protection" and "Add to Wallet."

Note: WalletConnect users on MetaMask are not supported.

Rabby Wallet (Manual Setup)
1. Go to the PancakeSwap MEV Guard page.
2. Click "Enable MEV Protection."
3. In Rabby Wallet settings, navigate to "Add Network" and enter the provided PancakeSwap MEV Guard RPC details.

Start Using MEV Guard Today

Activate PancakeSwap MEV Guard now to secure your trades and enjoy a seamless trading experience on the BNB Chain.
